company_description: Cegid is a leading provider of cloud business management solutions for finance (treasury, tax, ERP), human resources (payroll, talent management), CPAs, retail and entrepreneurial sectors. With a solid full cloud business model, Cegid provides long term commitment to its customers, superior and distinctive experiences and helps companies of all sizes accelerate their digital business transformation, locally and worldwide. Cegid combines a forward looking and pragmatic approach of the business with strong capacity to innovate, an in-depth expertise in new technologies and a unique understanding of regulations and compliance. In today’s rapidly changing world, Cegid makes more possible by helping customers unleash their potential thanks to innovative and purposeful business solutions.\ \ Bolstered by its strong international ambition and reach, Cegid has 4,400 employees and sells its solutions in 130 countries. Unifrog is a whole-school careers and destinations platform used by 2,500+ schools across the globe. \ \ The platform brings together English-taught undergraduate programmes in the UK, Europe, Asia, Australasia and the Middle East as well as faculties in Canada, and every college in the US. It also allows students to compare apprenticeships, School Leaver Programmes, and Further Education courses in the UK, as well as MOOCs worldwide. \ \ Once they've decided on a pathway, Unifrog makes it easy for students to record their activities and competencies and create and send applications.\ \ For teachers and counselors, Unifrog streamlines the entire progression process, allowing them to track and manage students' progress all in one place. The process of writing references and letters of recommendation is simplified with oversight of all students' application lists with a breakdown of requirements and a live status of where each application is at every step of the way. \ \ For a free demonstration please go to: www.unifrog.org or email simran@unifrog.org.

We started Jscrambler in 2010 to solve an important yet overlooked security problem. Client-side web applications were (and still are) mostly exposed, leaving them vulnerable to compromise. We found no good solution to protect our own app, so we created one - and built a company around it.\ Fast forward to now. Our security solutions have expanded to include all client-side web apps, from original code to third-party integrations. Organizations can innovate as often as the business demands while we provide continuous protection. \ We’re technologists at heart who understand the value of innovation. Our software products are developed entirely in-house by experts focused solely on the client-side. We don’t have a portfolio of disparate products or tools that only provide ‘checklist’ security. We simply have the most complete and mature solutions for protecting JavaScript-based web apps. \ Our customers include the FORTUNE 500, retailers, airlines, banks, and other enterprises whose success depends on safely engaging with their customers online. We keep these interactions secure so they can continue to innovate without fear of damaging their revenue source, reputation, or regulatory compliance.

We help businesses benefit from the involvement of a top quality businessman at a price that even the smallest business can afford.\ \ In some cases we make formal board placements, other times we operate in less formal positions. Unlike consultants who come into a business, make recommendations or complete a task, and then go; or employees who gradually lose their ability to view matters objectively; our members sit on the ‘rim’ of the business, neither in it nor outside of it. \ \ Consequently we bring independent status and free thinking along with a willingness to say what we think whilst being genuinely interested in the long term success of the business.\ \ The precise role we perform will differ from business to business from: acting as an experienced sounding board; opening doors and making connections; providing expert advice; helping to formulate company strategy and business plans; supporting the process of raising funding or assisting with specific one off tasks such as succession planning, acquisition, exit, and geographical expansion.\ \ We believe it is the first UK business that has been set up and structured specifically with the objective to bring the benefits of non-executive directors/services to SME’s. \ \ Where we differ is:\ •	we are focused on adding significant value to the businesses with which we work and being honest enough to walk away where we do not believe we can add value.\ •	we do not charge placement fees \ •	we are very cost efficient because we normally work on the basis of spending a small amount of time over a longer period. \ •	we do not normally do things for you, what we do is help you to do what you do better. This approach is not only cost efficient, it ensures that the improvements made are owned by you and your management team and are therefore sustainable.
